ndyFamily.jpg" />
<p>When the dad of a young family is given a year to live, what do you tell the kids? At four and six they swallow just about anything. They believe in Santa Claus, the Tooth Fairy, and Leprechauns. So what's a few more lies? Well in my family's case, everything, because reality would prove how ugly and messy life could get.<br />
<br />
<em>Cancer Spoken Here</em> is a (yet-to-be published) memoir about how our family began to speak the truth to our children and how we kept it up until the bitter end. It is the story of why I would do it the same way in a heartbeat and why I am an advocate for open dialogue in the face of disease. In the old days, we use to whisper about cancer. Today, we have banished the 'shhhh-factor' and can pull up a chair for cancer at the family table.<br />
